Measurement conducted with Hornet. Difficulty getting Hornet ‘Drive Control’ to engage. Troubleshooting did not reveal issues/cause. It just began working. Used first CC. Typical Heading Error: < 1.084°. Turbulence and/or turbidity was too great for StreamPro to perform MBT and Moving Boat Method. Transducer could not effectively penetrate water column. Switched to Section-by-Section.  Difficulty getting >30 valid ensembles within 4 minutes with ‘Water depth source: Bottom Track’. Strategy was to use ‘Water depth source: Bottom Track’ for the standard 40sec or until a depth was detected and then switch to ‘Water depth source: Manual Depth’ and enter the detected depth. This worked well. Profile looks accurate for location. Significant debris/anchor ice at times. Especially at LB. Could not dodge it all and boat fins were inevitably, not ideally deployed all the time. Two panels <30 valid ensembles due to debris/time constraints. Sources:Manual

Clothesline set-up 10m U/S of bridge. Eight Compass Calibrations were attempted. Despite getting ‘dark green’ bars for most attempts, errors exceeding 1° persisted. Some debris was unavoidable during calibration attempts but thought is there was some metallic interference at this exact location. Attempt transect at different location next time. Compass Calibration (10:11:45) passed (Vector Addition Of Single And Double Cycle Errors: 1.085°). Four Moving Bed Tests (loop) were attempted. The first three were all disrupted due to debris (ice and wood) and not used. Loop 003 indicated a moving bed and an ‘Estimated % Correction’ of 3.208 and was applied to all transects. Change due to suggested Extrap automatic fit is >1% (1.55% with Power/Power 0.1053). Power/Power  with exponent 0.1053 is recommended and applied. Sources:Import,Manual

Compass calibration (Vector Addition Of Single And Double Cycle Errors: 1.019°). Moving bed was detected with a loop test (% correction=2.75%). Transects 000-007 attempted to avoid bad ensembles/missing data and ambiguity velocities due to shallow depth and turbulence by boulders (left distance=13m). Transects 008 & 009 included the majority of the LB (left distance=2m). Interesting to note that despite an increase in bad ensembles for 008 & 009, total Q was comparable. When utilizing all 10 transects Delta Q exceeds 5% for transects 000, 003 & 005 (-6.09, -6.63 & +5.58 respectively). As well, left Q exceeds 5% of total Q for transects 000-007 (on average 10%). Above values are calculated prior to change due to Extrap. Change due to suggested Extrap automatic fit is >1% (+1.18% with Power/Power 0.1059) and therefore applied. For next measurement attempt a new location. Sources:Import
